    <section xml:id="Header-Identity-configuration-options">  
        <title>Header Identity Configuration Options</title>
        <para>The Header Identity Filter is added to a Repose deployment as a filter (header-identity) via the System Model Config.</para>
        <para>An example configuration is provided: Example Header Identity Configuration
            Header Identity can be configured by editing the header-identity.cfg.xml file. The user can specify the following information:</para>
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <guibutton>&lt;source-headers&gt;</guibutton>
                        : List of headers to identify the incoming
                        user. </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                   <guilabel>&lt;header&gt;</guilabel>
                                   : Header to identify incoming user. </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                   <itemizedlist>
                                   <listitem>
                                   <para><guilabel>id</guilabel> -
                                   This header key is applied to the
                                   x-pp-group header. The header value
                                   associated with this key is applied
                                   to the x-pp-user header.</para>
                                   </listitem>
                                   <listitem>
                                   <para>
                                   <guilabel>quality</guilabel> -
                                   Quality assigned to users found in
                                   the request headers.Â If no quality
                                   is set, Repose will default this
                                   value to 0.1</para>
                                   </listitem>
                                   </itemizedlist>
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
    </section>
    
